The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 September is 75,077 (8,653.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 September, there were 1,913 new confirmed cases (220.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 September, there were 1,617 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 18% (296 extra cases).
